We, Jenny and I went to Mississippi State for college and we met our freshman years,

29
00:02:20.180 --> 00:02:23.500
there's a whole story there, but I won't bore you with.

30
00:02:23.500 --> 00:02:30.260
We met our freshman year in a campus ministry that we attended.

31
00:02:30.260 --> 00:02:35.180
Of course, this was the first time we were living away from home.

32
00:02:35.180 --> 00:02:41.940
And we were very committed to our walk as Jesus followers.

33
00:02:41.940 --> 00:02:47.460
And we were committed to sharing our faith with students on campus.

34
00:02:47.460 --> 00:02:54.020
I think it was our sophomore year that we had a good friend in our ministry

35
00:02:54.020 --> 00:02:57.820
who was dating a guy who was not a Christian.

36
00:02:59.740 --> 00:03:03.860
And she had conversations with him, but eventually she wanted someone else to

37
00:03:03.860 --> 00:03:06.700
talk to him about following Jesus.

38
00:03:07.820 --> 00:03:10.620
And I was glad to do it.

39
00:03:10.620 --> 00:03:12.180
I was comfortable sharing my faith.

40
00:03:13.180 --> 00:03:19.660
And I had struck up already struck up a friendship with this with this guy.

41
00:03:19.660 --> 00:03:26.740
And so we agreed to meet even though this was about 50 years ago.

42
00:03:28.020 --> 00:03:30.500
I remember this occasion very clearly.

43
00:03:31.980 --> 00:03:35.620
We met on a stage in the church auditorium.

44
00:03:35.620 --> 00:03:37.700
Nobody else was there.

45
00:03:37.700 --> 00:03:41.620
And I was confident I was prepared for this conversation.

46
00:03:42.100 --> 00:03:45.580
And when we started the conversation, he started with a request.

47
00:03:45.580 --> 00:03:50.140
He said, so tell me about this guy, Jesus.

48
00:03:54.340 --> 00:03:57.340
Well, I was not prepared for that request.

49
00:03:59.620 --> 00:04:02.580
I was well prepared for the question, how do I become a Christian?

50
00:04:03.980 --> 00:04:06.780
