52
00:04:16.620 --> 00:04:18.100
I remember the occasion clearly.

53
00:04:18.100 --> 00:04:21.260
I remember the room where we sat and his question.

54
00:04:21.620 --> 00:04:24.660
But you know, I don't remember my answer at all.

55
00:04:26.820 --> 00:04:28.820
I think my pride has blocked it out.

56
00:04:29.860 --> 00:04:35.580
What I do remember is there was a lot of hymning and hawing, a lot of us and well.

57
00:04:37.780 --> 00:04:42.780
Fortunately, his faith journey did not depend on my preparation or my competence

58
00:04:42.780 --> 00:04:44.180
and sharing my faith.

59
00:04:44.180 --> 00:04:46.780
And he still became a Jesus follower.

60
00:04:46.780 --> 00:04:50.180
But this event taught me something very important.

61
00:04:51.180 --> 00:04:57.180
It taught me that the foundation of our faith includes an understanding of who Jesus is.

62
00:04:58.180 --> 00:04:59.180
It seems simple.

63
00:05:00.180 --> 00:05:04.780
I wish I had something like, you know, the statement here to share with him.

64
00:05:05.780 --> 00:05:06.780
I could have said this.

65
00:05:06.780 --> 00:05:14.780
There's certainly nothing in the statement that I didn't know at the time, couldn't talk about or didn't believe.

66
00:05:15.780 --> 00:05:19.780
I believed all of it and certainly knew all of the stories.

67
00:05:20.780 --> 00:05:27.780
But I was really not prepared, you know, to coherently talk about who Jesus was with somebody in a conversational way.

68
00:05:28.780 --> 00:05:29.780
Of course, I was young.

69
00:05:29.780 --> 00:05:42.780
As we're going through this firm foundation series where this is our fifth of the nine core beliefs that we have.

70
00:05:43.780 --> 00:05:54.780
But I think there's a tendency as we think through these nine core beliefs, there's a tendency to see them as kind of disconnected pieces.

71
00:05:55.780 --> 00:06:05.780
But I hope that it doesn't escape your attention the interconnectedness and sequencing of these core beliefs.

72
00:06:06.780 --> 00:06:07.780
So far we've covered God.

73
00:06:08.780 --> 00:06:14.780
We've covered the scriptures, which is God's word, humanity, sin and now Jesus.

74
00:06:16.780 --> 00:06:20.780
But consider the following just as kind of a thought experiment here.

75
00:06:20.780 --> 00:06:23.780
Consider the following as a summary of these core beliefs.

76
00:06:24.780 --> 00:06:32.780
And as I say this, I want you to see the five that we've covered so far as we as as they sequence through this.

77
00:06:33.780 --> 00:06:41.780
In the beginning God, the creator and sustainer of all things created all we see and don't see through the power of his word.

78
00:06:43.780 --> 00:06:48.780
In the ultimate act of his love, he created humans in his image.

79
00:06:48.780 --> 00:06:59.780
Although humans were offered eternal life with God, they chose instead to rebel, which resulted in sin and death entering the world.

80
00:07:00.780 --> 00:07:05.780
The sin problem could not be solved by humans and could only be solved by God himself.

81
00:07:06.780 --> 00:07:16.780
To that end and in his love and mercy, the father sent Jesus to die on the cross and then by the power of his word raised him from the dead.

82
00:07:17.780 --> 00:07:27.780
So did you hear the sequence? God, his word, the scriptures, humanity, sin and now we talk about Jesus.

83
00:07:28.780 --> 00:07:31.780
So we have nine core beliefs and we covered four of them.

84
00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:38.780
So now we come to the fifth core belief, which is right in the middle of the nine.

85
00:07:39.780 --> 00:07:47.780
So as Westerners, we when we list things, we tend to list the most important either first or last.

86
00:07:48.780 --> 00:07:51.780
And that's pretty typical in our culture.

87
00:07:52.780 --> 00:08:02.780
But if you pay close attention to the Bible, Hebrew writers, both old and New Testament, tend to put the preeminent in the center.

88
00:08:03.780 --> 00:08:17.780
So considering the following, just to make the point, the center of the Torah is Leviticus and the center of Leviticus is chapter 29, which talks about the day of atonement.

89
00:08:18.780 --> 00:08:24.780
Many scholars believe the day of atonement is the center of the Torah, the center of the center.

90
00:08:25.780 --> 00:08:30.780
The tabernacle was in the center of the camp of the Israelites as they were going to the Promised Land.

91
00:08:31.780 --> 00:08:36.780
And the tenta meeting or what we might call the Holy of Holies was in the center of the tabernacle.

92
00:08:37.780 --> 00:08:45.780
And in the center of the tenta meeting or Holy of Holies was the Ark of the Covenant, the center of the center of the center.

93
00:08:46.780 --> 00:08:53.780
Unless you think that this is just an Old Testament thing, the center of the Sermon on the Mount is the Lord's Prayer.

94
00:08:54.780 --> 00:09:00.780
Jesus died in the center between the two thieves on the cross.

95
00:09:01.780 --> 00:09:05.780
So I don't know if this was intended, Brandon, but I'm going to give you credit.

96
00:09:06.780 --> 00:09:12.780
So take all the credit that our core belief about Jesus is in the center of our nine.

97
00:09:13.780 --> 00:09:16.780
And to think about it, this is the way it should be.

98
00:09:17.780 --> 00:09:25.780
This is the story of the Bible from Genesis to Revelation, the story that Jesus is in the center.

99
00:09:26.780 --> 00:09:30.780
So just to make this point, consider Colossians 1.

100
00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:36.780
If you have your Bible, you can turn to Colossians 1 starting in verse 15.

101
00:09:37.780 --> 00:09:44.780
It says, and as I'm reading this notice the number of times Paul says all things.

102
00:09:46.780 --> 00:09:52.780
Starting in verse 15, he is the image of the invisible God, the firstborn of all creation.

103
00:09:53.780 --> 00:09:58.780
For by him all things were created in heaven and earth, visible and invisible,

104
00:09:59.780 --> 00:10:04.780
whether thrones or dominions or rulers or authorities, all things were created through him and for him.

105
00:10:04.780 --> 00:10:10.780
And he is before all things and in him all things hold together.

106
00:10:11.780 --> 00:10:13.780
And he is the head of the body, the church.

107
00:10:14.780 --> 00:10:19.780
He is the beginning, the firstborn of the dead, that in everything he might be preeminent.

108
00:10:20.780 --> 00:10:27.780
And in him all the fullness of God is pleased to dwell and through him to reconcile to himself all things,

109
00:10:28.780 --> 00:10:32.780
whether on earth or heaven, making peace by the blood of his cross.

110
00:10:32.780 --> 00:10:41.780
It is only fitting that Jesus is the center of our nine core beliefs because he is in the center of all things.

111
00:10:43.780 --> 00:10:51.780
So we have this statement of core belief in Jesus, but it's important for us to have certainty in that statement.

112
00:10:52.780 --> 00:10:57.780
Because we're committing our lives to this, we need to have certainty.

113
00:10:58.780 --> 00:11:03.780
The New Testament writers wrote about this certainty in the early years of the church.

114
00:11:04.780 --> 00:11:11.780
There were many people including the apostles who saw Jesus teach, walk the earth, perform miracles.

115
00:11:12.780 --> 00:11:20.780
And in 1 Corinthians 15 it says there were more than 500 people who saw Jesus after he rose from the dead.

116
00:11:20.780 --> 00:11:32.780
Most of those were early disciples, were members in first century churches and they would travel around to these churches as eye witnesses talking about what they saw.

117
00:11:35.780 --> 00:11:44.780
But as the years went on many of these eye witnesses died and there were more and more Christians that had not seen Jesus

118
00:11:44.780 --> 00:11:50.780
and more and more churches that didn't have any of these 500 eye witnesses to give testimony.

119
00:11:51.780 --> 00:12:01.780
So when Peter wrote his letter 35 years or so after Jesus died, he was aware that his readers needed certainty.

120
00:12:02.780 --> 00:12:06.780
And frankly this is important for us, 2,000 years later.

121
00:12:07.780 --> 00:12:13.780
So listen to what Peter says in 2 Peter 1 starting in verse 16.

122
00:12:14.780 --> 00:12:23.780
For we did not follow cleverly devised myths when we made known to you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ.

123
00:12:24.780 --> 00:12:27.780
But we were eye witnesses of His majesty.

124
00:12:28.780 --> 00:12:34.780
For when we received honor and glory from God the Father and the voice was born to Him by the majestic glory.

125
00:12:34.780 --> 00:12:37.780
This is my beloved son whom I am well pleased.

126
00:12:38.780 --> 00:12:45.780
We ourselves heard this very voice born from heaven for we were with Him on the holy mountain.

127
00:12:46.780 --> 00:12:57.780
And we have the prophetic word more fully confirmed to which you will do well to pay attention as a lamp shining in a dark place until the day dawns and the morning store rises in your hearts.

128
00:12:57.780 --> 00:13:07.780
Knowing this first of all that no prophecy of scripture comes from someone's own interpretation for no prophecy was ever produced by the will of man.

129
00:13:08.780 --> 00:13:11.780
But men spoke from God as they were carried along by the Holy Spirit.

130
00:13:12.780 --> 00:13:25.780
So I have known some atheists in my day and when it comes to Jesus they might agree that there was a man named Jesus who walked on this earth.

131
00:13:26.780 --> 00:13:31.780
They might believe the stories about him were interesting and maybe even compelling.

132
00:13:33.780 --> 00:13:37.780
But they would not believe that the claims that Jesus made were true.

133
00:13:39.780 --> 00:13:43.780
But Peter says that we don't follow cleverly devised myths.

134
00:13:44.780 --> 00:13:49.780
When I talk to atheists that's a lot of times similar kinds of words that they would use.

135
00:13:49.780 --> 00:13:55.780
It's all kind of made up by his followers after the fact.

136
00:13:56.780 --> 00:14:00.780
Peter said I was there at his baptism and I was there at his transfiguration.

137
00:14:01.780 --> 00:14:06.780
I heard the voice say this is my son whom I love.

138
00:14:07.780 --> 00:14:10.780
But he makes another argument that connects to one of our other core beliefs.

139
00:14:11.780 --> 00:14:18.780
He says that we have certainty in Jesus because of the scriptures both Old and New Testament that are written by men.

140
00:14:19.780 --> 00:14:23.780
Not by their own interpretation that they are inspired.

141
00:14:25.780 --> 00:14:32.780
We also have 1 Peter chapter 1 verse 8 and 9 where Peter talks about this topic as well and relate to us.

142
00:14:33.780 --> 00:14:38.780
He says though you have not seen him you love him.

143
00:14:39.780 --> 00:14:46.780
And though you do not now see him you believe in him and rejoice with joy that is inexpressible and filled with glory.

144
00:14:46.780 --> 00:14:50.780
Obtaining the outcome of your faith the salvation of your souls.

145
00:14:51.780 --> 00:14:55.780
There is a good lead on to next week when we talk about salvation.

146
00:14:56.780 --> 00:15:02.780
Peter's audience is like us. They have never seen Jesus in person.

147
00:15:03.780 --> 00:15:06.780
But Peter says we can have certainty in the story of Jesus.

148
00:15:07.780 --> 00:15:15.780
And after these verses he says the prophecies about Jesus are for us to give us certainty about Jesus.

149
00:15:16.780 --> 00:15:21.780
And therefore we can love him. We can believe in him. We can have faith in him.

150
00:15:22.780 --> 00:15:32.780
Now let's take a few moments to look at John's prophetic poem in John chapter 1.

151
00:15:33.780 --> 00:15:36.780
You can find it in your worship guide as well.

152
00:15:37.780 --> 00:15:40.780
But let's take a second to read that and then we'll talk a few minutes about it.

153
00:15:40.780 --> 00:15:42.780
John 1.1.

154
00:16:11.780 --> 00:16:15.780
He was not the light but he came to bear witness about the light.

155
00:16:16.780 --> 00:16:19.780
The true light which gives light to everyone was coming into the world.

156
00:16:20.780 --> 00:16:23.780
He was in the world and the world was made through him.

157
00:16:24.780 --> 00:16:25.780
Yet the world did not know him.

158
00:16:26.780 --> 00:16:29.780
He came to his own and his own people did not receive him.

159
00:16:30.780 --> 00:16:35.780
But to all who did receive him who believed in his name he gave the right to become children of God.

160
00:16:35.780 --> 00:16:41.780
Who were born not of blood nor of the will of the flesh nor of the will of man but of God.

161
00:16:42.780 --> 00:16:47.780
And the word became flesh and dwelt among us and we have seen his glory.

162
00:16:48.780 --> 00:16:51.780
Glory is the only son from the Father full of grace and truth.

163
00:16:52.780 --> 00:17:01.780
John bore witness about him and cried out this is he whom I said he who comes after me ranks before me and because he was before me.

164
00:17:02.780 --> 00:17:06.780
For from his fullness we have all received grace upon grace.

165
00:17:07.780 --> 00:17:11.780
For the law was given through Moses grace and truth came through Jesus Christ.

166
00:17:12.780 --> 00:17:15.780
No one has ever seen God the only God who is at the Father's side.

167
00:17:16.780 --> 00:17:17.780
He has made him known.

168
00:17:18.780 --> 00:17:25.780
Now before we look at the content or we'll pull out some things from the content of this poem.

169
00:17:26.780 --> 00:17:28.780
Let's notice something about the structure.

170
00:17:28.780 --> 00:17:32.780
So this is a highly structured poem.

171
00:17:33.780 --> 00:17:37.780
There are two sections the first section verses one through 13.

172
00:17:38.780 --> 00:17:51.780
And in this section John is poetically describing Jesus incarnation but he's using the words of the creation event of Genesis one and two.

173
00:17:52.780 --> 00:17:54.780
So right you see it in the beginning right.

174
00:17:54.780 --> 00:17:58.780
Genesis one one and we have the word.

175
00:17:59.780 --> 00:18:03.780
Then we have the light and we have the darkness.

176
00:18:04.780 --> 00:18:09.780
So all of those are words that we see in the Genesis creation account.

177
00:18:10.780 --> 00:18:14.780
Then the second section and starting in verse 14 goes 14 to 18.

178
00:18:15.780 --> 00:18:23.780
And in this section John is poetically describing Jesus incarnation in the language of something else from the Old Testament.

179
00:18:24.780 --> 00:18:26.780
And that is the tabernacle.

180
00:18:29.780 --> 00:18:33.780
So this word dwell in verse 14 where it says.

181
00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:37.780
Dwelled with us that word dwell means tent.

182
00:18:38.780 --> 00:18:43.780
It's the same word in the Greek version of the Old Testament that was used to describe the tabernacle.

183
00:18:44.780 --> 00:18:48.780
This could say he tended with us.

184
00:18:48.780 --> 00:18:53.780
So there's mention of glory which is a big part of the story around the tabernacle.

185
00:18:54.780 --> 00:18:57.780
There's mention of the law through Moses which of course is another part of that story.

186
00:18:58.780 --> 00:19:02.780
And then no one's seeing God which is another part of the story when Moses wants to see God.

187
00:19:03.780 --> 00:19:07.780
There's this mention about people not seeing God face to face.

188
00:19:09.780 --> 00:19:12.780
So both sections have a mention of John the Baptist.

189
00:19:12.780 --> 00:19:15.780
It's kind of weird because that's why you can see there's two sections.

190
00:19:16.780 --> 00:19:21.780
The first section has a mention of John the Baptist and the second section has a mention of John the Baptist.

191
00:19:22.780 --> 00:19:28.780
And then finally after two sections then we have a very interesting concluding sentence.

192
00:19:30.780 --> 00:19:31.780
So look at it.

193
00:19:32.780 --> 00:19:34.780
I didn't know this until I was preparing for this lesson.

194
00:19:35.780 --> 00:19:36.780
It's very interesting.

195
00:19:36.780 --> 00:19:39.780
The last sentence says he has made him known.

196
00:19:41.780 --> 00:19:45.780
Now presumably the he is the son and the him is the father in this sentence.

197
00:19:46.780 --> 00:19:50.780
But apparently they didn't know this but in Greek the sentence actually doesn't have a direct object in Greek.

198
00:19:52.780 --> 00:19:56.780
When they translated the Bible into English they just added a direct object in Greek.

199
00:19:57.780 --> 00:19:59.780
And then they translated the Bible into English.

200
00:20:00.780 --> 00:20:02.780
And then they translated the Bible into English.

201
00:20:03.780 --> 00:20:07.780
When they translated the Bible into English they just added a direct object, the him,

202
00:20:08.780 --> 00:20:10.780
because in the context he's talking about the father.

203
00:20:11.780 --> 00:20:16.780
And so they added a direct object so that in English we read he has made him known.

204
00:20:17.780 --> 00:20:19.780
But in Greek there's no him.

205
00:20:20.780 --> 00:20:26.780
So if you read the sentence in Greek it's a sentence that like trails off without an end.

206
00:20:27.780 --> 00:20:31.780
The sentence would read, actually it's not a sentence but it would read,

207
00:20:32.780 --> 00:20:36.780
he has made known dot dot dot.

208
00:20:39.780 --> 00:20:42.780
So it begs the reader to question what has he made known?

209
00:20:43.780 --> 00:20:47.780
What has he made known about the father which he's just talking about?

210
00:20:48.780 --> 00:20:53.780
So this poem is a prologue to the Gospel of John.

211
00:20:54.780 --> 00:20:57.780
And it's a book about Jesus.

212
00:20:58.780 --> 00:21:03.780
So John in the structure of this poem and then this sentence that doesn't end,

213
00:21:04.780 --> 00:21:09.780
he's inviting us to read to find out what Jesus is going to make known.

214
00:21:12.780 --> 00:21:13.780
He's going to make known?

215
00:21:14.780 --> 00:21:15.780
Well, keep reading.

216
00:21:17.780 --> 00:21:19.780
There's a lot of interesting things we could talk about.

217
00:21:19.780 --> 00:21:25.780
But let's pull out a few truths from this passage as we look at it.

218
00:21:26.780 --> 00:21:29.780
First of all, John is saying that if you want to fully understand who Jesus is,

219
00:21:30.780 --> 00:21:32.780
you have to go all the way back to the beginning.

220
00:21:33.780 --> 00:21:36.780
Now, this is not the way I grew up.

221
00:21:37.780 --> 00:21:44.780
The way I grew up, I grew up significantly downplaying the role of the Old Testament

222
00:21:45.780 --> 00:21:46.780
in understanding who Jesus was.

223
00:21:46.780 --> 00:21:52.780
I knew there were prophecies and they were important in validating Jesus,

224
00:21:53.780 --> 00:21:57.780
what he did and his status as the Messiah.

225
00:21:58.780 --> 00:22:03.780
But that's about it if I've been using the Old Testament to understand about Jesus.

226
00:22:04.780 --> 00:22:05.780
But John is saying something very different.

227
00:22:06.780 --> 00:22:09.780
He's saying the story of Jesus starts in Genesis 1.

228
00:22:10.780 --> 00:22:17.780
And the implication is then the whole Old Testament is centered on the story of Jesus as well.

229
00:22:18.780 --> 00:22:19.780
So that's one.

230
00:22:20.780 --> 00:22:23.780
Secondly, John is saying that Jesus was both fully God and fully human.

231
00:22:24.780 --> 00:22:27.780
We see that in verse 1, the word was God.

232
00:22:28.780 --> 00:22:30.780
And then in verse 14, the word became flesh.

233
00:22:31.780 --> 00:22:33.780
Fully God, fully human.

234
00:22:33.780 --> 00:22:39.780
Thirdly, John makes the point that Jesus is God's Son.

235
00:22:40.780 --> 00:22:42.780
It's not the only place it's mentioned, but it is mentioned in this poem.

236
00:22:43.780 --> 00:22:45.780
We see that in verse 14 and verse 18.

237
00:22:46.780 --> 00:22:51.780
And then finally, John is expanding our view of reality.

238
00:22:52.780 --> 00:22:55.780
So he does that in at least three ways.

239
00:22:56.780 --> 00:22:57.780
I'll just mention three.

240
00:22:58.780 --> 00:22:59.780
Expanding our normal sense of reality.

241
00:22:59.780 --> 00:23:09.780
First, notice John says in the first verses that the word was with God and the word was God.

242
00:23:10.780 --> 00:23:11.780
Right?

243
00:23:12.780 --> 00:23:13.780
Now think about that.

244
00:23:14.780 --> 00:23:15.780
How does that work?

245
00:23:16.780 --> 00:23:19.780
How is something with something and it's the thing as well?

246
00:23:20.780 --> 00:23:21.780
It makes no sense.

247
00:23:22.780 --> 00:23:27.780
John is inviting his readers into a different sense of reality.

248
00:23:27.780 --> 00:23:31.780
The word was with God and the word was God.

249
00:23:33.780 --> 00:23:35.780
Secondly, we've already mentioned this.

250
00:23:36.780 --> 00:23:38.780
Jesus was fully God and fully human.

251
00:23:39.780 --> 00:23:41.780
So we've come to accept this truth.

252
00:23:42.780 --> 00:23:43.780
It's in our core belief.

253
00:23:45.780 --> 00:23:49.780
But Bible scholars have been debating what this actually means.

254
00:23:50.780 --> 00:23:51.780
How does this work?

255
00:23:52.780 --> 00:23:54.780
That Jesus is fully God and fully human.

256
00:23:54.780 --> 00:23:55.780
Right?

257
00:23:56.780 --> 00:24:00.780
We've been talking about that since the beginning of time.

258
00:24:01.780 --> 00:24:04.780
It's interesting but hard to grasp.

259
00:24:05.780 --> 00:24:08.780
And then finally, notice what John the Baptist says in the second section.

260
00:24:09.780 --> 00:24:13.780
He says that Jesus was after him and Jesus was before him.

261
00:24:14.780 --> 00:24:19.780
So again, how is something after something and before something at the same time?

262
00:24:19.780 --> 00:24:23.780
So John is just blowing our minds with this poem.

263
00:24:24.780 --> 00:24:29.780
And then it finishes with an incomplete sentence to encourage us to read on.

264
00:24:30.780 --> 00:24:32.780
Read the story. Keep reading the story.

265
00:24:33.780 --> 00:24:37.780
And when we keep reading, we see Jesus lives a sinless life.

266
00:24:38.780 --> 00:24:41.780
We see him suffer at the hands of earthly authorities.

267
00:24:42.780 --> 00:24:46.780
We see him be obedient to his father even unto death and the cross.

268
00:24:46.780 --> 00:24:51.780
And we see him raised from the dead on the third day.

269
00:24:52.780 --> 00:24:57.780
So John and the other gospel writers give us a certainty in who Jesus is.

270
00:24:58.780 --> 00:25:02.780
But I'm here to tell you that it is important to have a certainty in who Jesus is.

271
00:25:03.780 --> 00:25:07.780
But it is at least as important, maybe more important,

272
00:25:08.780 --> 00:25:12.780
to have a certainty of who Jesus is to me.

273
00:25:12.780 --> 00:25:21.780
The story of Jesus is a story of God coming to earth to invite us into a relationship with God.

274
00:25:22.780 --> 00:25:25.780
It's important to believe that Jesus is King of Kings.

275
00:25:26.780 --> 00:25:29.780
But it's more important that he is my King.

276
00:25:30.780 --> 00:25:33.780
It's important to believe that Jesus is Lord of Lords.

277
00:25:34.780 --> 00:25:36.780
But it's more important that he is my Lord.

278
00:25:37.780 --> 00:25:39.780
That he is the Lord of my life.

279
00:25:39.780 --> 00:25:41.780
That he is the Lord of my life.

280
00:25:42.780 --> 00:25:45.780
And even though I'm thankful for the gift of adoption into God's family,

281
00:25:46.780 --> 00:25:50.780
that I still view myself as a servant of God.

282
00:25:51.780 --> 00:25:54.780
It's important to believe that Jesus died on the cross.

283
00:25:55.780 --> 00:25:59.780
But it's more important to understand that he died on the cross for me.

284
00:26:01.780 --> 00:26:08.780
And even though I'm thankful for the gift that he gave to me on the cross,

285
00:26:09.780 --> 00:26:11.780
I have been crucified with Christ.

286
00:26:12.780 --> 00:26:14.780
I'm no longer I who live but Christ who lives in me.

287
00:26:15.780 --> 00:26:20.780
And the life I now live in the flesh, I live by faith in the Son of God who loved me and gave himself for me.

288
00:26:21.780 --> 00:26:24.780
It's important to believe that Jesus was raised from the dead.

289
00:26:25.780 --> 00:26:28.780
But it's more important to believe that as Jesus was raised from the dead,

290
00:26:29.780 --> 00:26:35.780
that I have been raised to walk a new life and ultimately will be raised in new creation.

291
00:26:36.780 --> 00:26:41.780
So this cannot be overstated. Our belief in Jesus is important.

292
00:26:42.780 --> 00:26:44.780
But notice what James said.

293
00:26:45.780 --> 00:26:47.780
He said, you believe that God is one?

294
00:26:49.780 --> 00:26:50.780
You do well.

295
00:26:51.780 --> 00:26:53.780
But even the demons believe and shudder.

296
00:26:54.780 --> 00:26:56.780
Notice what John says at the end of his gospel.

297
00:26:57.780 --> 00:27:02.780
Now Jesus did many other signs in the presence of the disciples which are not written in this book.

298
00:27:02.780 --> 00:27:06.780
But these are written so that we may believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God.

299
00:27:07.780 --> 00:27:11.780
And that by believing, we can have life in his name.

300
00:27:12.780 --> 00:27:18.780
As James says, believing is good, but it's God's desire and intention that we have eternal life with him.

301
00:27:19.780 --> 00:27:22.780
Jesus' invitation to us is that we come to him.

302
00:27:23.780 --> 00:27:27.780
Matthew 11, he says, come to me all you who labor and are heavy laid.

303
00:27:27.780 --> 00:27:33.780
Now I'll give you rest, take my yoke upon you and learn from me, for I am gentle and lowly in heart

304
00:27:34.780 --> 00:27:36.780
and you will find rest for your souls.

305
00:27:37.780 --> 00:27:39.780
For my yoke is easy, my burden is light.

306
00:27:40.780 --> 00:27:45.780
And then notice what Scripture says at the very end of the Bible in Revelation chapter 22.

307
00:27:46.780 --> 00:27:53.780
Jesus talking to John says, I, Jesus, have sent my angel to testify to you about these things for the churches.

308
00:27:54.780 --> 00:27:59.780
I am the root and the descendant of David and the bright morning star.

309
00:28:00.780 --> 00:28:08.780
The spirit and the bride say, come and let the one who hears say, come and let the one who is thirsty come.

310
00:28:09.780 --> 00:28:14.780
Let the one who desires to take the water of life without price.

311
00:28:16.780 --> 00:28:20.780
We've been talking about Jesus at the center of all things.

312
00:28:20.780 --> 00:28:25.780
Paul uses the word preeminent, at least in English, that's our word.

313
00:28:26.780 --> 00:28:30.780
Paul says that Jesus is preeminent, but Peter uses a different metaphor.

314
00:28:31.780 --> 00:28:34.780
Peter said that Jesus is the cornerstone.

315
00:28:36.780 --> 00:28:40.780
But again, not to belabor the point, it's important to realize Jesus is the cornerstone.

316
00:28:41.780 --> 00:28:45.780
But it's more important that Jesus is the cornerstone of my life.

317
00:28:46.780 --> 00:28:51.780
It's important that all parts of my life are built on the cornerstone of Jesus.

318
00:28:52.780 --> 00:28:54.780
That my marriage is built on the cornerstone of Jesus.

319
00:28:55.780 --> 00:28:58.780
That my parenting is built on the cornerstone of Jesus.

320
00:28:59.780 --> 00:29:05.780
That my interactions with the world are built on the cornerstone of Jesus.

321
00:29:06.780 --> 00:29:10.780
And that my mission and fellowship in his church are built on the cornerstone of Jesus.

322
00:29:11.780 --> 00:29:13.780
Quoting from the Old Testament, Peter said,

323
00:29:14.780 --> 00:29:18.780
Behold, I'm laying in Zion a stone, a cornerstone chosen and precious,

324
00:29:19.780 --> 00:29:22.780
and whoever believes in him will not be put to shame.

325
00:29:23.780 --> 00:29:29.780
So our core belief is that God in the person of Jesus came down to us.

326
00:29:30.780 --> 00:29:33.780
We can have certainty in this. We can have certainty.

327
00:29:34.780 --> 00:29:39.780
It is true. And that in full assurance, we can have faith in Jesus as a cornerstone of our life.

328
00:29:40.780 --> 00:29:43.780
With him. Let's pray.

329
00:29:48.780 --> 00:29:52.780
Thank you, Father, for your mercy and care for us.

330
00:29:53.780 --> 00:29:56.780
Thank you, Jesus, for coming and showing us how to live in this world.

331
00:29:57.780 --> 00:30:00.780
Thank you for offering yourself in death for us.

332
00:30:01.780 --> 00:30:05.780
Sanctify us by your spirit so that we will offer ourselves in faith to you.

333
00:30:06.780 --> 00:30:07.780
In Jesus' name, amen.

